Senate President Ahmad Lawan has congratulated the Muslim Ummah for the successful completion of the Holy Month of Ramadan. Lawan, in a statement by his Special Adviser (Media), Ola Awoniyi, yesterday, called on the Muslim faithful to imbibe the lessons of self-restraint, sacrifice, charity and sharing with their neighbours and the needy.   Uzodimma promises more safety for Muslims     Abiodun preaches against immorality, get-rich syndrome     IG orders security at prayer grounds, others   He said:  Let’s continue to show these in our daily lives. We should also continue to pray for security and peace in our beloved country, Nigeria and in the world at large. “As Nigerians, let us engage in what is right and avoid whatever is forbidden by our faith, and be good representatives of our faith. We should continue to abhor whatever threatens peace and embrace whatever strengthens the unity of our nation. “The National Assembly will continue to play its role, in partnership with the Executive, towards achieving our national dreams and aspirations.”